cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the application of quantization methods to GANs, which are primarily used in computer vision tasks such as image generation and classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the instability of training GAN models, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the experiments are conducted on image datasets, which also aligns with the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
